article.headline: Indiana 102, S. Carolina St. 60
article.story: BLOOMINGTON, Ind. -- Christian Watford scored 22 points as Indiana rolled to a 102-60 victory over South Carolina State in the Las Vegas Classic on Sunday. Matt Roth added 14 points for the Hoosiers (9-2), who are 9-0 at home this season and have won 10 straight overall in Bloomington. Brandon Riley scored 12 point to lead the Bulldogs (4-6). Both teams will travel to Las Vegas this week for the final two games of the tournament. The Hoosiers set a season-high for points and scored at least 100 for the second time in six games. Watford scored 14 points in the first half to help Indiana take a 43-35 lead into intermission.
